@NODE BML "NetDOCK-2 Help Document: The Blitz-Mailing-List"
 ---------------=======+++* @{FG HIGHLIGHT}The Blitz-Mailing-List@{FG TEXT} *+++========---------------

 In case you didn't know, NetDOCK-2 was programmed in Blitz BASIC 2.
 However, if it wasn't for this superb mailing list, NetDOCK-2 wouldn't
 even be here today! It is basically an e-mail group which offers advice on
 everything Blitz. You send an e-mail to the list, and everyone who has
 subscribed to the list will get that mail. Then they are free to offer
 advice on it, which is also sent to the list.

 To subscribe to the list, send a BLANK e-mail (with no subject either) to:

   blitz-list-subscribe@netsoc.ucd.ie

 And then follow the instructions on the e-mail which should be returned to
 you in about 10 mins.

 Once again, thanx to everyone on the Blitz Mailing List for all the help
 and advice on NetDOCK-2 probs. CHEERS!!!!
@ENDNODE
@NODE HISTORY "NetDOCK-2 Help Document: History"  
 ---------------==========+++++**** @{FG HIGHLIGHT}History@{FG TEXT} ****+++++==========---------------

 V1.25
 -----

  Just some minor rewrites to inform user of what goes on. No bugs 
  discovered (or fixed!).

 V1.2
 ----
  
  Found a bug which swapped image/path around, rendering ND2 unusable.
  Fixed the above bug.

 V1.1
 ----

  Implemented window-wrap (cheers Chris) in case there isn't enough room
  for all the icons.
  No bugs as yet.

 V1.0
 ----
 
  First non-beta. Everything going well. No bugs, images work fine, but 
  program crashes if the window can't be displayed (for whatever reason)

 V0.97ß
 -----

  Last beta-version. Crushed all major bugs. Everything else works fine.

 Versions lower than these were wiped out in a hard drive crash, so my
 records are lost. Utter barsteward or what?
@ENDNODE
